screen-translator (2.0.3-1) stable; urgency=low

  * Implemented Hybrid Clipboard Monitor for Wayland:
    - CLIPBOARD: Uses native GTK event-driven owner-change (synced flawlessly by XWayland).
    - PRIMARY: Uses a 1-second interval wl-paste poll (GNOME blocks XWayland from reading primary).
  * Removed Gdk.Seat global grab from TranslationPopup to fix focus/defocus issues and prevent lag.

 -- sonnn <sonnn@localhost>  Wed, 17 Jun 2026 17:15:00 +0700

screen-translator (2.0.2-1) stable; urgency=low

  * Removed wl-paste entirely! GNOME Wayland lacks --watch support.
  * Reverted to pure, passive GTK clipboard monitoring.
  * XWayland (GDK_BACKEND=x11) perfectly synchronizes the clipboard
    from Wayland to GTK, so native GTK owner-change signals work
    flawlessly without any polling, subprocesses, or lag.

 -- sonnn <sonnn@localhost>  Wed, 17 Jun 2026 17:10:00 +0700

screen-translator (2.0.1-1) stable; urgency=low

  * Replaced wl-paste polling with wl-paste --watch to fix system lag
  * Fixed popup icon blinking in dock caused by continuous process spawning
  * Restored fully passive, event-driven clipboard monitoring on Wayland

 -- sonnn <sonnn@localhost>  Wed, 17 Jun 2026 16:28:00 +0700

screen-translator (2.0.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Major popup refactor — eliminates window-stack thrash that caused other
    apps (Chrome, VS Code, etc.) to repeatedly lose/regain focus and the
    sidebar icon to flash on/off whenever auto-translate was enabled.
    - Switched popup type hint to NOTIFICATION (was TOOLTIP)
    - Removed per-show present()/set_keep_above; popup is mapped via show()
      only, so Mutter no longer reshuffles the focus stack on every result
    - Added skip_taskbar/skip_pager/focus_on_map hints
    - Widget tree built once and reused via a Gtk.Stack (loading/error/result)
      instead of destroyed+recreated for every selection
  * Replaced 100 ms mouse-position polling with a passive Gdk.Seat grab for
    outside-click dismiss.
  * Added request token: stale translation results from earlier selections
    are now dropped instead of overwriting the popup with old content.
  * Clipboard monitor wires through user-configured delay/min/max from config
    (previously hardcoded), exposes stop() for clean shutdown, and uses
    Event.wait() so the polling threads exit promptly on quit.
  * Renamed misleading internal `_delay_ms` (stored seconds) to `_settle_seconds`.

 -- sonnn <sonnn@localhost>  Fri, 05 Jun 2026 12:00:00 +0700

